<subSubSection lastPageId="52" lastPageNumber="53" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="51.[151,1436,1775,2016]" lastBlockId="52.[151,1436,151,248]" lastPageId="52" lastPageNumber="53" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1991,2016]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
A species of 
<taxonomicName box="[484,592,1992,2015]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cepolidae" genus="Owstonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[484,592,1992,2015]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Owstonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with LL pattern 
<typeStatus box="[791,839,1992,2016]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">type</typeStatus>
1; lower limb margin of preopercle without spines; dorsal fin III, 19; no dark premaxillary stripe; adults with 34–35 teeth in outer row of each premaxilla; papillae in slight depression behind tip of ascending process of premaxillae with a cluster of about 5 minute papillae present between the posterior pair of relatively large papillae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
